value.body:
The Texas Rangers are 33-10 (.767) in one-run games this season. This would stand as a modern record for winning percentage in one-run games, besting the 2012 Orioles, who were 29-9 (.763).

http://images.performgroup.com/di/library/sporting_news/a3/fa/texasrangers-getty-ftr-091516jpg_9u1oo1fjvsue1twr2494i9qcn.jpg?t=766994815

But if we dig deep into the archives of baseball history, we learn that this is actually the best record since the 1890 Brooklyn Bridegrooms, who were 14-4 (.778) in one-run games en route to an overall 86-43 (.667) record and the National League pennant. **Source / Read More...** sportingnews.com
